abstract: LinkedIn reports second-quarter revenue of $712 million, up 33 percent from year-earlier period and beating analyst expectations; results are nonetheless insufficient to stem investor skepticism as shares fall 7.7 percent in after-hours trading.
lead_paragraph: LinkedIn’s second-quarter results beat Wall Street’s expectations on all fronts, but the signs behind the numbers seemed to worry investors.

headline.main: Linkedin Beats Expectations, but Its Shares Fall Anyway
headline.print_headline: Linkedin Beats Expectations, but Its Shares Fall Anyway

snippet: LinkedIn’s second-quarter results beat Wall Street’s expectations on all fronts, but the signs behind the numbers seemed to worry investors.
